    <h1>Hyposthesis and Theory</h1>
      <p>In scientific reasoning, a hypothesis is constructed before an applicable research has been done. A theory, on other hand, is supported by eveidence:<br />
      it's a principle formed as an attempt to explain things that have already been substantiated by data.</p>
